Termix - A wrapper of chroot/proot to run linux on termux.

Usage: termix <init|boot> <bootdir>

See also:
  QQGroup: 494453985
  https://busybox.net
  https://github.com/proot-me/proot
  https://github.com/95e2/linux-on-termux


********* FOR EXAMPLE

1. sh install.sh

2. mkdir alpine && cd alpine

3. wget -O - http://mirrors.ustc.edu.cn/alpine/v3.7/releases/armhf/alpine-minirootfs-3.7.0-armhf.tar.gz | tar xzvpf -

4. cd ../ && termix init alpine

5. termix boot alpine

******** END OF FOR EXAMPLE OF TERMIX


********* USEFUL GUIDE OF CHROOT VERSION

There are some useful tools in the chroot-script,
You can use it to fix some issues in the linux.

For example:
  * chroot-script/patch/group-patch.sh
    It can slove normal user can not access /sdcard or can not connect to internet.

  * chroot-script/busybox-static
    It can install a busybox on your devices that if you don't have any busybox installed.

********* END OF USEFUL GUIDE OF CHROOT VERSION
